Clearwire Corp. , the fourth-
generation wireless carrier, declined to its lowest level in
more than a year in Nasdaq Stock Market trading after partner
Sprint Nextel Corp. said it has no plans to buy the company.  Clearwire has fallen 11 percent in the last two days,
dropping to its  lowest price  since July 2009. The Kirkland,
Washington-based companyâ€™s shares declined 36 cents, or 6.3
percent, to $5.34 at 4 p.m. New York time.  Sprint, which owns 54 percent of Clearwire, made its
